The paper deals with distributed network computing and protocols for verifying network configurations using distributed certificates that can be verified locally. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also addresses the issue of privacy in certificate verification, which is a concern in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of certificates and verification also involves Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the complexity of the certificates and their verification, which is relevant to Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
